This project is a masterclass in High-Performance FinOps. We are building a system that can handle the massive traffic of a Black Friday sale while ensuring the infrastructure remains lean, automated, and cost-efficient. We aren't just building a website; we are building a global, self-healing business engine.

Here is the blueprint for everything we will accomplish across the five phases of this project.

1. The Project Roadmap

Phase 1: Global Data Persistence (The Foundation): Establishing an RDS Multi-AZ database in the primary region with a Cross-Region Read Replica in the secondary region. We also implement S3 Intelligent-Tiering for automated storage cost optimization.

Phase 2: High-Performance Compute (The Spot Strategy): Building an Auto Scaling Group (ASG) that utilizes a Mixed Instances Policy. This allows us to use up to 90% cheaper Spot Instances for the bulk of our traffic while keeping a small baseline of On-Demand instances for stability.

Phase 3: Statelessness & Global Caching (The Performance Tier): Decoupling the application by moving shopping carts to DynamoDB On-Demand and using CloudFront to cache product images globally. This reduces the load on our servers and speeds up the user experience.

Phase 4: Decoupled Business Logic (The Event-Driven Tier): Using SQS and Lambda to process orders. This ensures that even if the database is busy during a traffic spike, no orders are lost; they simply wait in a queue for a few milliseconds until they can be processed.

Phase 5: Global Failover & DR (The Pilot Light): Setting up Route 53 Health Checks and Failover routing. We will simulate a total regional collapse and automate the promotion of our Oregon replica to a primary database.


