The full Service Stack:

| Service     | Specific Implementation Goal                       | FinOps Value                                   |
| ----------- | -------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| VPC         | Multi-Tier networking in two regions               | Standardized, secure foundation                |
| S3          | Storing product images with Intelligent-Tiering    | Zero-effort cost reduction for old data        |
| RDS (MySQL) | Multi-AZ for local HA; Cross-Region Replica for DR | Reliable data without Aurora's premium cost    |
| EC2         | Spot Instances + Graviton processors               | Massive savings (up to 90%) on compute         |
| ASG         | Target Tracking & Mixed Instance Policies          | Scales up for sales, scales to min for savings |
| ALB         | Distributing traffic across private app subnets    | High availability with built-in health checks  |
| DynamoDB    | On-Demand capacity for session/cart storage        | Pay only for what you use; scales to infinity  |
| SQS         | Buffering order messages to prevent DB overloads   | Decouples services; prevents Thundering Herds  |
| Lambda      | Serverless inventory updates                       | Zero idle cost; charges only when processing   |
| Route 53    | Failover Routing & Health Checks                   | Automated disaster recovery                    |
| CloudFront  | Global Content Delivery Network (CDN)              | Offloads 80%+ of image traffic from servers    |
| CloudWatch  | Dashboards and Alarms                              | Identifies Zombie resources and idle waste     |

